# ============================================================
# Prevent committing local environment configuration files
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# These files often contain secrets (API keys, passwords) or
# personal / machine‑specific settings. They should NEVER be
# pushed to GitHub.
# ============================================================
.env*
*.local
# ============================================================
# Prevent committing Python virtual environments
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Some tools in Codespaces automatically create you a 'venv' or
# '.venv' folder. These contain hundreds of temporary Python files
# that do NOT belong in a Java/Node project.
# ============================================================
.venv/
venv/
# ============================================================
# Prevent committing system installer files
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Example: 'packages-microsoft-prod.deb' appears when installing
# Microsoft packages inside Codespaces. These files are large,
# binary, and not part of your project code.
# ============================================================
*.deb
